{
  "stem": "13817.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the beginning of-- of '38, he and his family [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] moved or immigrated to Colombia, South America.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was the first one of the family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, my mother was thinking of immigrating too, but she had two young boys, a widow who-- who had a business what was still fairly good.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After my brother completed his apprenticeships, he-- he was in the business already taking over, so everything was still going.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was still a young kid.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was 16, 17.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so she-- the idea was to immigrate after I completed my education after my brother got established.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so the urgency for-- to immigrate didn't start till 1938 after the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the Kristallnacht I experienced-- first of all when it started I was in Cologne.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was in the apprenticeship.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this company I was working for was also naturally a Jewish company because I couldn't work for anybody else.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at that time, in the early afternoon when it started, I left work and went to the train to go home.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "To be sure that I wasn't too harassed, I left the train one station before Kerpen and walked, which was about two and a half miles, walked to home through the back ways because I didn't know what was going on in Kerpen.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When I got home around 4, 5 o'clock, everything was still fairly quiet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then all of a sudden the hordes of the Nazis came, the drunks came, [INAUDIBLE] all drunks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The first thing they did, they tore the synagogue part.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They took out the benches and put them in the middle of the street.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They tore the-- the prayer shawls to pieces and put everything in one pile and made a big bonfire there.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
